The evidence with the title 'Live fact-checking the second GOP presidential debate | politifact ' says Sep 15, 2015  ... As president , Reagan also raised the debt ceiling 18 times between february 1981 and september 1987. What's more, Reagan "understood repeatedly that when the deficit started to get out of control, that for him to make a deal he would have to propose both spending cuts and tax increases," said Obama. 
